      <unittitle encodinganalog="245">George S. Morris Papers <unitdate type="inclusive" encodinganalog="245$f" normal="1852/1889">1852-1889</unitdate>, <unitdate type="inclusive" encodinganalog="245$f" normal="1910/1915">1910-1915</unitdate>, <unitdate type="bulk" encodinganalog="245$g" normal="1852/1889">1852-1889</unitdate></unittitle>
      <abstract>Professor of philosophy at Johns Hopkins University and University of Michigan. Correspondence; notes and lectures on philosophical topics, notably ethics, political philosophy, logic and aesthetics; diary and journal, including account of European trip, 1866-1867; photographs; and later materials collected by Robert M. Wenley preparatory to writing a biography of George S. Morris, 1910-1915.</abstract>
